dataAttributeValues.Question21: All HP equipment checked and free of damage
dataAttributeValues.Question22: Is it possible for the work to be carried out at in a controlled environment such as a welding bay?
dataAttributeValues.Question23: Is it possible for the work to be carried without having to carry out the lifting operation, if not have adequate access and egress means been agreed with all parties for the lifting equipment?
dataAttributeValues.Question26: Is it possible for the work to be carried out at ground level, if not have adequate access methods been made available?
dataAttributeValues.Question13: Has sufficient lighting been provided in the case of dark areas, dusk, night and dawn?
dataAttributeValues.Question14: Special tools/equipment requirements assessed & equipment provided?
dataAttributeValues.Question15: Is there safe means of access to the work area?
dataAttributeValues.Question16: Have barriers or covers been used to prevent falls through openings in the floor/ceiling?
dataAttributeValues.Question17: Have methods of waste disposal been agreed?
dataAttributeValues.Question18: Are all tools and equipment in good working order and suitable for the job?
dataAttributeValues.Question19: Have methods of cleaning any spillages been agreed?
dataAttributeValues.Question20: Is any lone working to take place and if so, have suitable arrangements been made for this?
dataAttributeValues.Question3: Is the workforce qualified to carry out the task?
dataAttributeValues.Question4: Is work being carried out at height? If yes a WAH PTW should be issued.
dataAttributeValues.Question5: Isolated electrical supply? Work in accordance with current Electricity at Work Regs.
dataAttributeValues.Question6: Are personnel aware of means of escape and method of raising alarm?
dataAttributeValues.Question7: Is confined space working necessary? If so, a Confined Spaces PTW is required.
dataAttributeValues.Question8: Are personnel aware of first aid reporting procedures?
dataAttributeValues.Question9: Isolator locked off / tagged? Work in accordance with Electricity at Work Regs. Safe Working Practices HSG 85.
dataAttributeValues.Question10: When working outdoors assess weather conditions to ensure it is safe to carry out the work.
dataAttributeValues.Question11: Have you been provided with copies of certification?
